OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,469,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1774721160
OL,3,CFarage dismisses Reform candidate
OL,4,C'Nazi salute' as 'Fawlty Towers
OL,5,Cimpression'
OL,7,FVisiting Sunderland to launch his
OL,8,Fparty's local election campaign there,
OL,9,FNigel Farage was asked by ITV News
OL,10,Fabout the photo and whether Mr Edwards
OL,11,Fwould still be a candidate.
OL,13,F"It was a Fawlty Towers impression"
OL,14,Fsaid Mr Farage.
OL,16,F"The context I have been told, it was
OL,17,Ftaking a Basil Fawlty sketch, and
OL,18,Fthat's why he did it. He's a human
OL,19,Fbeing."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/5
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,469,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1774721160
OL,3,CFarage dismisses Reform candidate
OL,4,C'Nazi salute' as 'Fawlty Towers
OL,5,Cimpression'
OL,7,FPressed further by ITV News on whether
OL,8,FCorey Edwards would remain a
OL,9,Fcandidate, Mr Farage attempted to bat
OL,10,Fthis aside.
OL,12,F"I get the point - it looks terrible.
OL,13,FThings in isolation often do. I
OL,14,Fwouldn't approve of it", before
OL,15,Fcomparing it to the "far more serious"
OL,16,Fcase of a Plaid Cymru candidate
OL,17,Fstepping down for an offensive tweet.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/5
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
